<div class="app-card-container">
  <div class="card">
    <h1>About Me</h1>

<hr>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4">

    <%= image_tag "profile.jpg", width: 300, alt: "Profile Image", class: 'profile-img' %>

    <div class="skills">
      <% @skills.each do |skill| %>
        <div class="skill">
          <h4><%= skill.title %></h4>
          <div class="progress">
            <div
              class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-warning"
              role="progressbar"
              aria-valuenow="<%= skill.percent_utilized %>"
              aria-valuemax="100"
              style="width: <%= skill.percent_utilized %>%"
            ></div>
          </div>
        </div>

      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-md-8">
    <p class="justified">Since a beginner in development can't say much about how long he's been working, I think that the next best thing is to tell how little time he needed to learn what he did. For me, it took just four months to learn HTML5, CSS, Javascript, Ruby on Rails and Bootstrap 4 and be comfortable with it. Of course, my knowledge of these technologies is far from advanced but I wouldn't say it's just basic either.</p>
    <p>But what stands out as a preffered technology by far is Ruby on Rails. </p>

      <button
        class='btn btn-primary'
        type='button'
        data-toggle='collapse'
        data-target='#jobHistory'
        aria-expanded='false'
        aria-controller='jobHistory'
      >
          Job History
      </button>

      <button
        class='btn btn-primary'
        type='button'
        data-toggle='collapse'
        data-target='#education'
        aria-expanded='false'
        aria-controller='education'
      >
          Education
      </button>

    </p>

    <p>
      <div class="collapse" id='jobHistory'>
        <div class="card card-block">
          School 1
        </div>
        <div class="card card-block">
          School 2
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="collapse" id='education'>
        <div class="card card-block">
          Job 1
        </div>
        <div class="card card-block">
          Job 2
        </div>
      </div>

    </p>
    <p>
  </div>

</div>
  </div>
</div>
